### Bug Description

1. Void flow - For connectors that support instant payout only
* Create and confirm the payout 
* Make a void call
This make a void call to the connector - instead it should have been cancelled at hyperswitch end (because for the ones that support instant payouts , no call was made to the connector yet)

2. In case of payouts via wallets -  at the time of serializing and constructing the response - no matter which wallet was used we always got the paypal struct in response:
```

"payout_method_data": {
        "wallet": {
            "email": null,
            "telephone_number": null,
            "paypal_id": null
        }
    }

```

This is because the struct for WalletAdditionalData was marked untagged and all the fields for PaypalAdditionalData was optional, so every struct was getting serialized to paypal's.
```

#[derive(
    Eq, PartialEq, Clone, Debug, Deserialize, Serialize, FromSqlRow, AsExpression, ToSchema,
)]
#[diesel(sql_type = Jsonb)]
#[serde(untagged)]
pub enum WalletAdditionalData {
    /// Additional data for paypal wallet payout method
    Paypal(Box<PaypalAdditionalData>),
    /// Additional data for venmo wallet payout method
    Venmo(Box<VenmoAdditionalData>),
    /// Additional data for Apple pay decrypt wallet payout method
    ApplePayDecrypt(Box<ApplePayDecryptAdditionalData>),

```

### Expected Behavior

1. In this case, we shouldn't make the call to the connector, instead cancel it at our end.
To address this, we are adding a check - we wont make a void call to the connector if the status is `RequiresFulfillment` and it supports instant payout.
2. To address this response handling, we are changing the way PaypalAdditionalData struct is parsed, For payout via paypal, only one of the field should be present - so either we will receive email or telephone or paypal_id.
We are changing the struct to enum :
```

#[serde(tag = "flow_type", rename_all = "snake_case")]
pub enum PaypalAdditionalData {
    /// Email linked with paypal account
    #[schema(example = "john.doe@example.com")]
    Email {
        /// Email linked with paypal account
        email: MaskedEmail
    },
    /// mobile number linked to paypal account
    #[schema(example = "*******3349")]
    TelephoneNumber {
        /// mobile number linked to paypal account
        telephone_number: MaskedPhoneNumber
    },
    /// id of the paypal account
    #[schema(example = "G83K*****HCQ2")]
    PaypalId {
        /// id of the paypal account
        paypal_id: MaskedBankAccount
    },
}

```

and the WalletAdditionalData would look like : 
```
pub enum WalletAdditionalData {
    ApplePayDecrypt(Box<ApplePayDecryptAdditionalData>),
    Paypal(Box<PaypalAdditionalData>),
    Venmo(Box<VenmoAdditionalData>),
}

```


### Actual Behavior

1. In this case, we shouldn't make the call to the connector, instead cancel it at our end.
To address this, we are adding a check - we wont make a void call to the connector if the status is `RequiresFulfillment` and it supports instant payout.
2. To address this response handling, we are changing the way PaypalAdditionalData struct is parsed, For payout via paypal, only one of the field should be present - so either we will receive email or telephone or paypal_id.
We are changing the struct to enum :
```

#[serde(tag = "flow_type", rename_all = "snake_case")]
pub enum PaypalAdditionalData {
    /// Email linked with paypal account
    #[schema(example = "john.doe@example.com")]
    Email {
        /// Email linked with paypal account
        email: MaskedEmail
    },
    /// mobile number linked to paypal account
    #[schema(example = "*******3349")]
    TelephoneNumber {
        /// mobile number linked to paypal account
